SIMPLE: diodon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diodon
<hw>Di"o*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>di-</grk> =
<grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <grk>'odoy`s</grk>, <grk>'odo`ntos</grk>, a
tooth: cf. F. <ets>diodon</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A genus of spinose, plectognath fishes, having the teeth of each
jaw united into a single beaklike plate. They are able to inflate the
body by taking in air or water, and, hence, are called
<altname>globefishes</altname>, <altname>swellfishes</altname>, etc.
Called also <altname>porcupine fishes</altname>, and <altname>sea
hedgehogs</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of whales.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diodont</ent>⟦br⟧
